      "amount": "1/4 cup",
      "notes": "chopped"
    },
    {
      "name": "crunchy bulgur",
      "amount": "1/2 cup",
      "notes": "cooked and cooled"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 425 degrees Fahrenheit.",
    "Wrap the chopped beetroot in foil and roast for 45 minutes, or until tender.",
    "Let the beetroot cool, then peel and chop it into small pieces.",
    "In a large bowl, whisk together the pomegranate molasses, lemon juice, olive oil, salt, black pepper, and sumac.",
    "Add the cooled beetroot, toasted pine nuts, and chopped parsley to the bowl and toss to combine.",
    "Stir in the cooked and cooled bulgur.",
    "Chill the salad in the refrigerator for at least 30 minutes to allow the flavors to meld.",
    "Serve the salad cold, garnished with additional parsley and pine nuts if desired."
  ],
